      • forEach

        public <H extends RowHandler<? super T>> H forEach(Reader reader,
                                                   H handle)
                                            throws IOException,
                                                   MappingException
        Description copied from interface: CsvMapper
        Will map each row of the content of reader to an object of type T and will pass that object to the handle via the RowHandler.handler(T t) call back.

        The method will return the handler passed as an argument so you can easily chain the calls like
        List<T> list = mapper.forEach(reader, new ListHandler<T>()).getList();

        Specified by:
        forEach in interface CsvMapper<T>
